Readily available features:
time = date in yearqtr format
short_term_i = short term interest rate
inf = inflation
target = target inflation
gdp = GDP, adjusted for inflation
gdppot = Potential GDP, adjusted for inflation
total_debt = Total debt of USA
unemployment_rate = Unemployment rate in the US

Engineered features:
crisis_dummy = Dummy variable that indicates whether the US was going through a crisis during the year or not.(9/11, market crash etc.)
recession_dummy = Dummy variable that indicates whether there was a recession or not.
inf_diff = The difference between actual inflation and target inflation, calculated as follows: inf - target 
outputgap = the Output gap of the USA, calculated as follows: (gdp-gdppot)/gdppot*100
